metadata.name: The Solitary Journey
metadata.description:
We all must, at some point, undertake our own individual journey through life, facing our own unique challenges and obstacles. 

As we journey alone, we come to realize that true strength is not the absence of vulnerability, but the ability to confront and overcome it.

It is in the moments of greatest loneliness and isolation that we are most likely to find our truest selves.

The journey may be tough, but the strength we gain from it is invaluable.
